        <h1 class="Heading1Chapter"><a name="kanchor4"></a>Planning a System</h1>
        <p>The planning and design stage is arguably the most important step in implementing <span class="VariablesProductName">DigitalEdge</span>. During this phase, you will gather all the details you need to configure <span class="VariablesProductName">DigitalEdge</span>. You must identify and understand:</p>
        <ul>
            <li value="1">Data sources and parsers</li>
            <li value="2">Fields/columns in each data table</li>
            <li value="3">Formats and transport mechanisms for each data source</li>
            <li value="4">Enrichment tables that will enhance your data feeds with additional information</li>
            <li value="5">Data sinks that will store your data</li>
            <li value="6">Applications that your users will need</li>
        </ul>
        <p>In addition, you must create a data blueprint for the new system by defining an <i>input model</i> that will serve as the normalized model for all incoming data. For more complex systems, you can iterate the design phase, changing and enhancing the data model as you test the system configuration. </p>
